<p>
‘|<hi rend="superscript">1</hi> In the name of God, the Compassionate, the Merciful.
|<hi rend="superscript">2</hi> [From ʿUmar b. Muslim to … ]d and Aḥmad and Fāṭima, the children of ʿUmar. |<hi rend="superscript">3</hi> [Peace be upon you. I praise for your sake G]od besides Whom there is no god but He.
|<hi rend="superscript">4</hi> [As for what follows, may God grant us and you the best of his health and may He perfect it in this world |<hi rend="superscript">5</hi> [and the hereafter … ] and God is blessed. Nothing happened to me after you (pl.), |<hi rend="superscript">6</hi> [except good things  … ] with the <emph rend="italics">ʿāmil</emph> of Ushmūn and you/I wrote  … |<hi rend="superscript">7</hi> [ … ] and you (sing.) have already written to me about the news concerning your condition… |<hi rend="superscript">8</hi> [ … ] … the <emph rend="italics">ʿāmil</emph> takes care of/has good intentions towards him/it |<hi rend="superscript">9</hi> [ … ] …’
	Back:
‘From ʿUmar b. Muslim to …’
</p>
</div>
